# RE_OS — Cline Rules
# Auto-read by Cline at session start. Follow these exactly.

## Before touching anything

Read in this order — all four, every session, no skipping:
1. CLAUDE.md — full project state, architecture, run commands
2. AGENTS.md — single backlog (check what is IN PROGRESS before picking a task)
3. CHANGELOG.md — top section is the current handoff; bottom has recent file changes
4. .cline_logs/CHANGELOG.md — your own last session log

If a task in AGENTS.md is marked IN PROGRESS, do not start it. Pick something else or ask Jinu.
If a file was changed in the last 24 hours (visible in CHANGELOG.md), read the full file before editing it.

## While working

- One task at a time. Finish and log before starting the next.
- Before editing any file: read its current state fully. No editing from memory.
- After every meaningful change: git commit (one-line message) + CHANGELOG.md entry.
- Never resolve an architectural conflict silently. Log both approaches, flag for Jinu.

## After every session — REQUIRED

Write a handoff block at the TOP of CHANGELOG.md (overwrite the previous one):

  ## Current Handoff -- Cline [DATE TIME IST]
  Status: in progress / complete / blocked
  Last files touched: [list]
  State: one honest sentence — does the code run? is the pipeline functional?
  Next action: exact first thing the next brain should do
  Open question for Jinu: [if any, else None]

Then add your session entry to .cline_logs/CHANGELOG.md using the format in that file.

## Hard limits — never without Jinu confirmation

- Edit .env or rotate API keys
- Drop or truncate any database table
- Delete anything in logs/, outputs/, or .cline_logs/
- Push to any remote repository
- Run docker compose down when Jinu may be mid-session
